-subscription-manager register --username devinder_lamba@bmc.com --password bmcAdm1n --auto-attach
-Install required packages: sudo yum install -y yum-utils device-mapper-persistent-data lvm2
-Set up the stable repository: sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo
-Enables the nightly repository: sudo yum-config-manager --enable docker-ce-nightly
-Enables the test repository: sudo yum-config-manager --enable docker-ce-test
-Disables the nightly repository: sudo yum-config-manager --disable docker-ce-nightly
-Install the latest version of Docker Engine - Community: sudo yum install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
-Install required packages: sudo yum install -y yum-utils device-mapper-persistent-data lvm2
-Update the yum cache: sudo yum makecache fast
-Install docker community edition package: sudo yum -y install docker-ce
-Start the docker service: sudo systemctl start docker
-Test your Docker CE installation: sudo docker run hello-world
-Check docker version: sudo docker version
-Adding your user to the “docker” group: sudo usermod -aG docker your-user
-Linux cowsay game: sudo docker run docker/whalesay cowsay Hello-World!